This paper deals with energy efficiency in wireless sensor networks, which is a topic closely related to network protocols and communication technologies. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the analysis of modulation schemes, which falls under the category of information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely sub-category. The use of mathematical models and optimization techniques in the analysis of energy efficiency suggests that cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) could also be a relevant sub-category. The paper also deals with system modeling and optimization, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and the use of experimental results suggests that cs.MM (Multimedia) could also be a relevant sub-category.
